eligibility_criteria.description:
Minimum age: 18 Years
Maximum age: 80 Years

Symptomatic or poorly controlled heart disease or had a heart attack or stroke within
             the last 6 month

Karnofsky >= 60% for subjects > 16 years of age and Lansky >= 50 for subjects =< 16 years of age; note: subjects who are unable to walk because of paralysis, but who are up in a wheelchair, will be considered ambulatory for the purpose of assessing the performance score
Patients with a history of allergic reactions to 13-cis-retinoic acid (CRA) or compounds of similar biologic or chemical composition to CRA
Participants who are pregnant or breast feeding
Patients with renal abnormalities requiring modification of radiation field (pelvic kidney, renal transplant, etc.)

Tumor assay profile must include on of the following: MammaPrint High, any ER status,
             any HER2 status, or MammaPrint Low, ER negative (<5%), any HER2 status, or MammaPrint
             Low, ER positive, HER2/neu positive by any one of the three methods used (IHC, FISH,
             TargetPrint)
Other serious concurrent illness or medical condition.

Uncontrolled intercurrent illness including, but not limited to, ongoing or active infection, symptomatic congestive heart failure (New York Heart Association class III and IV heart failure), unstable angina pectoris, cardiac arrhythmia, or psychiatric illness/social situations that would limit compliance with study requirements or concurrent medications that alter cardiac conduction

groups.description: Patients receive dacarbazine IV over 1-2 hours and bortezomib IV over 3-5 seconds weekly in the absence of disease progression or unacceptable toxicity.

interventions.name: Drug, Food, Chemical or Biomedical Material

groups.name: Treatment (dacarbazine, bortezomib)

groups.description: Participants received placebo administered by subcutaneous injection on Day 1 and at Month 6.
groups.name: Placebo

outcome_measures.analysis_method: Smoking abstinence as measured by the Society for Research on Nicotine and Tobacco Smoking Status Measure at 26 weeks following study treatment
outcome_measures.measure: Number of Patients with Smoking Abstinence

outcome_measures.analysis_method: Points estimate and exact confidence interval for the proportion of subjects who show 50% increase in PSADT will be reported.
outcome_measures.measure: PSADT response defined as a 50% increase in the PSADT compared to pre-enrollment PSADT (Arm A)
outcome_measures.time_frame: Up to 20 months after initial patient accrual
